FOR THE first time since Israel’s founding, efforts to form a government have failed. What will the resulting snap election mean for the prime minister, Binyamin Netanyahu? Alleged meddling in the Czech judiciary has sparked protests, as challenges to the rule of law proliferate in eastern Europe. And we visit winemakers in Crimea, who are struggling after the territory was annexed by Russia. Runtime: 21 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn